Berlusconi Says He’ll Discuss Bank Italy With Napolitano Today

-- B y   L o r e n z o   T o t a r o
-- 
2011-10-14T12:22:39Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-14/berlusconi-says-he-ll-discuss-bank-italy-with-napolitano-today.html
Prime Minister  Silvio Berlusconi 
said he will hold talks on the Bank of  Italy  today with
President Giorgio Napolitano. Berlusconi told reporters in  Rome 
today that he’ll nominate a successor to Governor  Mario Draghi 
by Nov. 1.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Lorenzo Totaro in Rome at 
 ltotaro@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
